HEADWORD: Pathogeny
<hw>Pa*thog"e*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The generation, and method of development, of disease;
<as>as, the <ex>pathogeny</ex> of yellow fever is unsettled</as>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>That branch of pathology which treats of the
generation and development of disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pathognomonic</ent>⟦br⟧
